      "span_text": "OH-NP and CO-NP were transformed into hydroquinone during the incubation with rat liver microsomes, and the formation of hydroquinone depended on both the microsomes and NADPH. As Ohe has shown,  in the ipso-metabolism reaction, the alkyl substituent is not eliminated and serves the ipso-addition product, and benzyl alcohol and benzophenone type phenol derivatives give hydroquinone by ipso-substitution."
